---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import LessonShell from "../../components/LessonShell.astro";
import FakeTerminal from "../../components/FakeTerminal.astro";
import Screencast from "../../components/Screencast.astro";
import { LESSONS } from "../../data/curriculum";

const lesson = LESSONS.find((l) => l.id === "code-slash")!;
---

<Layout title={`${lesson.title} · Learn AI`} description={lesson.blurb} currentId="code-slash">
    <LessonShell lesson={lesson}>
      <p>
        Every modern coding CLI has the same three extensibility primitives, with slight name variations.
        Drive the imitation: press <kbd>/</kbd>, type, hit Enter. Watch streaming + approval prompts.
      </p>

      <Screencast slot="code-loop" />

      <FakeTerminal cwd="~/my-project" />

      <h2>Try these</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><code class="inline">/agents</code> — list specialized assistants</li>
        <li><em>"fix the bug"</em> — the assistant reads files, runs tests, finds the cause</li>
        <li><em>"add a dark mode toggle"</em> — note the Allow/Deny prompt before any write</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="trio">
        <div>
          <h4>Slash command</h4>
          <p>Do this <em>action</em> now.</p>
          <small>Claude Code: <code class="inline">/plan</code> · Cursor: <code class="inline">@</code> · aider: <code class="inline">/add</code></small>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4>Agent / mode</h4>
          <p>Switch to this <em>persona</em>.</p>
          <small>Claude Code: agents · Cursor: modes · Codex: agents</small>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4>Skill / rule</h4>
          <p>Use this <em>recipe</em>.</p>
          <small>Claude Code: skills · Cursor: rules · aider: <code class="inline">.aider.conf</code></small>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2>Tool approval</h2>
      <p>Every CLI asks before touching your machine. The pattern is the same; the UI varies:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Claude Code:</strong> "Claude wants to do this — Allow / Deny"</li>
        <li><strong>Cursor:</strong> Agent mode shows a diff before applying</li>
        <li><strong>Codex CLI:</strong> "approval modes" — Suggest / Auto-Edit / Full-Auto</li>
        <li><strong>aider:</strong> shows diff + asks "Apply edit? (Y/n)"</li>
      </ul>
    </LessonShell>
</Layout>

<style>
  .trio {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin: 1.2rem 0;
  }
  .trio > div {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 0.8rem 0.9rem;
  }
  .trio h4 { margin: 0 0 0.25rem; font-size: 0.88rem; }
  .trio p { margin: 0 0 0.3rem; color: var(--ink-soft); font-size: 0.86rem; }
  .trio small { display: block; color: var(--ink-faint); font-size: 0.78rem; }
  @media (max-width: 600px) { .trio { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
</style>
